    1. CRITICAL The web auth model is not production-safe. The client reads
     NEXT_PUBLIC_EGP_TENANT_ID and NEXT_PUBLIC_EGP_API_BEARER_TOKEN and sends that bearer
     token on every request, which means auth is effectively a public browser-config secret
     instead of a real user/session model. The login page is also just a UI shell with no auth
     flow behind it. See apps/web/src/lib/api.ts:598 and apps/web/src/app/login/page.tsx:63.
  2. HIGH The worker/API boundary is drifting from the architecture you wrote down. The PRD
     says the worker should emit events/artifacts and the API should own state transitions,
     but the worker directly upserts projects and transitions closure state itself. See docs/
     PRD.md:443, apps/worker/src/egp_worker/workflows/discover.py:46, and apps/worker/src/
     egp_worker/workflows/close_check.py:51.
  3. HIGH Notifications and webhooks are still synchronous hot-path work. Webhook delivery
     retries inline, with network I/O and up to 3 attempts per target, and that path is called
     directly from core flows like run completion, document review approval, exports, and
     worker workflows. That couples customer webhook latency/failures to your core app latency
     and throughput. See packages/notification-core/src/egp_notifications/
     webhook_delivery.py:155, apps/api/src/egp_api/services/document_ingest_service.py:165,
     apps/api/src/egp_api/services/export_service.py:180, and apps/api/src/egp_api/services/
     run_service.py:99.
  4. HIGH Payment callback security has a config footgun. Callback routes bypass auth
     middleware, and callback-secret enforcement disappears if auth is disabled and no
     callback secret is set. That is too weak for a money-moving boundary. See apps/api/src/
     egp_api/main.py:228 and apps/api/src/egp_api/routes/billing.py:215.
  5. MEDIUM The runtime decomposition is ahead of the actual implementation. The worker
     entrypoint is basically a startup print plus symbol references, and the doc-processor is
     still mostly a facade/TODO. So the repo looks more service-oriented on paper than it is
     operationally. See apps/worker/src/egp_worker/main.py:11, apps/doc-processor/src/
     main.py:10, and apps/doc-processor/src/egp_doc_processor/processor.py:12.
